218
00:09:31,490 --> 00:09:33,250
Shut up, good-for-nothin' wimp!

219
00:09:33,250 --> 00:09:33,960
Go away!

220
00:09:35,710 --> 00:09:36,780
That hurt.

221
00:09:36,780 --> 00:09:37,770
What is this?

222
00:09:37,770 --> 00:09:39,150
My heart hurts.

223
00:09:39,580 --> 00:09:41,400
That kid's amazing.

224
00:09:41,400 --> 00:09:44,890
He only just met you, yet he can tell
that you're good-for-nothing and a wimp.

225
00:09:44,890 --> 00:09:45,390
Hey!

226
00:09:45,880 --> 00:09:49,230
With punks like these, tough talk won't work.

227
00:09:49,710 --> 00:09:50,540
Hey, you guys!

228
00:09:50,540 --> 00:09:51,470
Dyed blonde hair!

229
00:09:51,470 --> 00:09:52,570
He's got dyed blonde hair!

230
00:09:52,570 --> 00:09:54,230
What? You tryin' to threaten us?

231
00:09:54,670 --> 00:09:56,370
Y'all are bigger'n these kids,

232
00:09:56,370 --> 00:09:58,690
so can't ya be nice to 'em?

233
00:09:58,690 --> 00:09:59,990
C'mon, can't ya?

234
00:10:01,300 --> 00:10:02,810
If yer gonna say it that way...

235
00:10:04,120 --> 00:10:06,000
Say it on yer knees.

236
00:10:08,260 --> 00:10:09,830
Stop! Calm down, Hiro!

237
00:10:09,830 --> 00:10:10,740
Let me go!

238
00:10:10,740 --> 00:10:12,790
I'll show him how harsh society can be!

239
00:10:12,790 --> 00:10:13,920
*Snot-nosed punk = Mean kid

240
00:10:12,790 --> 00:10:13,920
Snot-nosed punk!

241
00:10:13,920 --> 00:10:15,100
Run away!

242
00:10:15,490 --> 00:10:18,560
Actually hitting a kid will
just cause more problems!

243
00:10:16,430 --> 00:10:17,880
Stupid violent adult!

244
00:10:19,030 --> 00:10:20,830
Yankee go home!

245
00:10:19,260 --> 00:10:23,500
Sensei, we were wantin' to play dodgeball here.

246
00:10:21,920 --> 00:10:23,500
Get out, outsider!

247
00:10:23,500 --> 00:10:26,060
Well, then, we can't back down now.

248
00:10:26,690 --> 00:10:28,650
These kids are counting on me.

249
00:10:28,650 --> 00:10:31,020
Now is the time to show some dignity!

250
00:10:31,560 --> 00:10:32,760
Hey, you boys!

251
00:10:32,760 --> 00:10:34,270
You say somethin', white noodles?

252
00:10:34,720 --> 00:10:36,780
White... noodles...?

253
00:10:37,850 --> 00:10:40,860
We're adults, so we don't use violence.

254
00:10:40,860 --> 00:10:43,900
However, if you guys throw your
weight around here any more,

255
00:10:43,900 --> 00:10:46,200
I'll have to make a phone call.

256
00:10:46,200 --> 00:10:48,080
What? Who're ya gonna call?

257
00:10:49,310 --> 00:10:50,170
The police!

258
00:10:50,460 --> 00:10:52,540
What makes ya think the police would come?!

259
00:10:53,080 --> 00:10:56,380
I'll give an anonymous tip that
you guys are bullying little kids.

260
00:10:57,070 --> 00:10:58,790
Getting arrested is embarrassing, y'know.

261
00:10:58,790 --> 00:11:00,140
It'll upset your parents, too.

262
00:11:00,140 --> 00:11:01,760
You'll be ruined for life.

263
00:11:02,090 --> 00:11:03,050
You see?!

264
00:11:03,050 --> 00:11:04,680
This is an adult tactic!

265
00:11:06,070 --> 00:11:07,390
So immature.

266
00:11:07,520 --> 00:11:10,050
Dang it, yer usin' dirty threats!

267
00:11:10,050 --> 00:11:11,220
Take this!

268
00:11:17,690 --> 00:11:20,450
You finished off my cell phone!

269
00:11:20,680 --> 00:11:22,130
What do ya mean, "finished"?

270
00:11:22,130 --> 00:11:23,870
It's just got poo on it.

271
00:11:24,180 --> 00:11:25,160
Don't give me that, you brat!

272
00:11:25,160 --> 00:11:26,480
Sure, it no longer works as a phone,

273
00:11:26,480 --> 00:11:29,040
but it's still served me faithfully
as a clock! And look at it now!

274
00:11:29,560 --> 00:11:31,380
Can't use it as a phone?

275
00:11:31,380 --> 00:11:33,170
You were trickin' kids, then!

276
00:11:33,170 --> 00:11:36,060
You insulted my phone,
so why are you getting mad?!

277
00:11:40,690 --> 00:11:41,990
Hiro, were you laughing?

278
00:11:41,990 --> 00:11:44,100
No, I'd never laugh at that.

279
00:11:47,650 --> 00:11:49,150
Ah, what're they doin'?

280
00:11:49,150 --> 00:11:50,760
Let's leave 'em and go play baseball.

281
00:11:50,760 --> 00:11:51,350
Wha?!

282
00:11:51,350 --> 00:11:52,200
Wait, Sensei!

283
00:11:52,200 --> 00:11:54,310
They're trying to ignore us!

284
00:11:54,310 --> 00:11:55,230
What?!

285
00:11:55,750 --> 00:11:57,030
Don't make me repeat myself!

286
00:11:57,030 --> 00:11:59,180
Use your own village's playground!

287
00:11:59,180 --> 00:12:00,050
Shut up!

288
00:12:00,050 --> 00:12:02,700
Middle schoolers took over our playground!

289
00:12:02,990 --> 00:12:05,950
A real tough-fightin' girl and a glasses girl.

290
00:12:06,650 --> 00:12:08,310
It's them...

291
00:12:08,310 --> 00:12:09,750
That ain't got nothin' to do with it!

292
00:12:09,930 --> 00:12:11,120
Get outta here!

293
00:12:11,330 --> 00:12:12,450
Naru!

294
00:12:12,450 --> 00:12:14,120
Hey! That's going too far!

295
00:12:14,530 --> 00:12:17,190
What? Didn't ya say adults ain't violent?

296
00:12:17,190 --> 00:12:19,070
If an adult from this village hits us,

297
00:12:19,070 --> 00:12:20,860
we're tellin' our parents!

298
00:12:20,860 --> 00:12:24,200
If an adult hits a kid,
that's who's goin' to the police!

299
00:12:24,340 --> 00:12:27,390
You'll get arrested for child abuse!

300
00:12:27,830 --> 00:12:29,720
If they put it that way, we can't argue.

301
00:12:30,070 --> 00:12:33,730
Right, an adult should never strike a child.

302
00:12:34,070 --> 00:12:37,360
Naru, they want to play baseball here.

303
00:12:37,910 --> 00:12:38,980
So let them play.

304
00:12:38,980 --> 00:12:40,010
Aww...

305
00:12:40,010 --> 00:12:42,570
You shoulda done that in the first place!

306
00:12:42,570 --> 00:12:44,200
They'll play their game.

307
00:12:44,770 --> 00:12:46,940
So how about we play dodgeball?

308
00:12:46,940 --> 00:12:47,950
Yeah.

309
00:12:48,920 --> 00:12:50,580
You were gonna yield this place to us!

310
00:12:51,110 --> 00:12:53,320
Play all the baseball you want.

311
00:12:53,320 --> 00:12:55,460
We're going to play our own game.

312
00:12:55,850 --> 00:12:57,870
Sensei and I will be outfielders.

313
00:12:57,870 --> 00:12:59,540
Get running, you guys.

314
00:13:00,090 --> 00:13:01,400
W-Wait, time out!

315
00:13:01,400 --> 00:13:02,340
We're playin' here!

316
00:13:02,560 --> 00:13:03,090
Here!

317
00:13:03,090 --> 00:13:03,630
Ow!

318
00:13:05,050 --> 00:13:06,320
That's our Sensei.

319
00:13:06,320 --> 00:13:07,890
Playing seriously against kids.

320
00:13:08,310 --> 00:13:10,120
It don't count if it don't hit us!

321
00:13:10,120 --> 00:13:10,920
Clumsy—

322
00:13:13,420 --> 00:13:15,020
Now, who's next?!

323
00:13:16,260 --> 00:13:17,990
He hit it back?!

324
00:13:17,990 --> 00:13:19,790
Get a grip, Sensei!

325
00:13:19,790 --> 00:13:21,230
If they take the ball, it's all over.

326
00:13:21,470 --> 00:13:23,430
Dang it, yer supposed to be adults!

327
00:13:23,430 --> 00:13:24,650
Why are ya takin' this seriously?!

328
00:13:25,110 --> 00:13:26,460
"Supposed to be adults"?

329
00:13:26,460 --> 00:13:27,200
Hardly.

330
00:13:28,500 --> 00:13:30,620
It's because we're adults!

331
00:13:32,990 --> 00:13:34,200
Take this, brat!

332
00:13:34,550 --> 00:13:35,790
Sensei, toss it here!

333
00:13:36,240 --> 00:13:38,380
I'm impressed they can
horse around in this heat.

334
00:13:38,710 --> 00:13:39,370
It's Akki!

335
00:13:39,370 --> 00:13:40,260
Akki!

336
00:13:40,260 --> 00:13:42,030
What're ya doin' out here?!

337
00:13:42,030 --> 00:13:44,260
Hey, I'm stuck on that game ya lent me!

338
00:13:44,530 --> 00:13:46,470
You guys! The battle's not over yet!

339
00:13:46,710 --> 00:13:48,250
Oh, it's okay now.

340
00:13:48,250 --> 00:13:49,970
We're gonna go play with Akki.

341
00:13:51,120 --> 00:13:53,710
Wait a minute. You're giving up that easily?!

342
00:13:53,710 --> 00:13:56,720
I'm sorry for interrupting your fun.

343
00:13:56,720 --> 00:13:58,270
Uh, no, it wasn't really...

344
00:13:58,750 --> 00:14:00,070
So long!

345
00:14:00,070 --> 00:14:01,270
We'll come again!

346
00:14:05,250 --> 00:14:08,710
Akki is amazingly mature.

347
00:14:08,710 --> 00:14:09,500
Yeah...

348
00:14:14,350 --> 00:14:15,450
Don't follow me.

349
00:14:16,050 --> 00:14:18,340
I'm heading back to my house.

350
00:14:18,340 --> 00:14:21,630
Aww! I wanna play more!

351
00:14:20,140 --> 00:14:21,630
Don't stretch it!

352
00:14:21,630 --> 00:14:22,130
By golly!

353
00:14:22,540 --> 00:14:24,380
Let's play Tarzan! Tarzan!

354
00:14:24,380 --> 00:14:24,880
Tarzan?

355
00:14:25,340 --> 00:14:27,140
We play it up that way!

356
00:14:27,140 --> 00:14:28,840
It's gobs of fun!

357
00:14:32,630 --> 00:14:34,350
Oh, all right.

358
00:14:34,350 --> 00:14:35,870
Just for a bit.

359
00:14:35,870 --> 00:14:38,440
Yay! This way, this way!

360
00:14:39,470 --> 00:14:40,150
Say...

361
00:14:40,480 --> 00:14:41,400
This is...

362
00:14:41,400 --> 00:14:44,660
the most realistic Tarzan setting I've ever seen.

363
00:14:45,410 --> 00:14:46,230
It's easy!

364
00:14:46,230 --> 00:14:47,360
No, it's not!

365
00:14:47,360 --> 00:14:49,410
Isn't that a real vine?!

366
00:14:49,410 --> 00:14:51,050
I'll show ya how it's done!

367
00:14:51,050 --> 00:14:52,450
Stop, it's dangerous!

368
00:14:52,860 --> 00:14:53,520
Hey!

369
00:15:00,300 --> 00:15:02,380
Just... like that...

370
00:15:02,660 --> 00:15:03,840
What'll I do?

371
00:15:03,840 --> 00:15:05,840
This doesn't look fun at all.

372
00:15:06,710 --> 00:15:08,750
Okay, it's yer turn next, Sensei!

373
00:15:08,750 --> 00:15:09,790
As if I could!

374
00:15:09,790 --> 00:15:11,540
Why not? It's real fun!

375
00:15:11,540 --> 00:15:13,350
Yer pretty lame for a grown-up!

376
00:15:13,350 --> 00:15:16,850
You wouldn't say that if you
had an adult's physique!

377
00:15:17,240 --> 00:15:18,700
It's completely impossible!

378
00:15:18,700 --> 00:15:21,270
There's no way this vine could
support an adult's weight.

379
00:15:21,730 --> 00:15:25,350
Though, if all of you could hang from
it at once, it'd be a different story.

380
00:15:27,830 --> 00:15:28,630
Oh, fine!

381
00:15:28,630 --> 00:15:30,080
So I was wrong!

382
00:15:30,080 --> 00:15:31,340
So, will ya do it too, Sensei?

383
00:15:31,340 --> 00:15:32,570
All right, all right.

384
00:15:32,880 --> 00:15:35,740
But I'm begging you, don't do
anything dangerous in front of me!

385
00:15:35,740 --> 00:15:38,590
All right! This'll be gobs of fun!

386
00:15:38,590 --> 00:15:40,810
You may be trying to convince me of that,

387
00:15:40,810 --> 00:15:42,540
but I'm not happy about it.

388
00:15:43,090 --> 00:15:46,430
As long as this vine is here,
they're going to get hurt someday.

389
00:15:46,430 --> 00:15:49,770
Sorry, kids, but I'm getting rid
of this dangerous toy.

390
00:15:50,130 --> 00:15:51,130
Yer rarin' to go!

391
00:15:51,480 --> 00:15:53,550
I'll pretend to swing, and tear it off!

392
00:15:57,070 --> 00:16:00,040
No, Sensei, you can't stretch it like that!

393
00:16:00,040 --> 00:16:01,560
Stop it!

394
00:16:01,560 --> 00:16:03,000
It'll tear!

395
00:16:03,000 --> 00:16:04,480
Don't!

396
00:16:04,480 --> 00:16:06,020
Everybody, stop!

397
00:16:24,940 --> 00:16:27,000
Are any of you guys hurt?

398
00:16:27,000 --> 00:16:28,050
Nope, we're fine!

399
00:16:28,050 --> 00:16:29,880
That was super scary!

400
00:16:30,530 --> 00:16:31,660
I thought I was gonna die!
I thought I was gonna die!

401
00:16:31,660 --> 00:16:32,840
I thought I was gonna die!
I thought I was gonna die!

402
00:16:33,020 --> 00:16:34,030
Sensei, yer bleedin'!

403
00:16:34,030 --> 00:16:35,240
You all right?!

404
00:16:35,240 --> 00:16:36,070
I'm fine.

405
00:16:36,070 --> 00:16:37,160
It's just a scratch.

406
00:16:37,160 --> 00:16:38,680
Ya need mugwort for that!

407
00:16:38,680 --> 00:16:40,680
Get lookin' for mugwort!

408
00:16:38,880 --> 00:16:40,040
No, that's okay!

409
00:16:40,040 --> 00:16:41,000
It's not that bad!

410
00:16:41,000 --> 00:16:41,580
Naru!

411
00:16:41,580 --> 00:16:42,520
I got mugwort!

412
00:16:43,580 --> 00:16:45,550
This medicine'll stop the bleedin'!

413
00:16:45,550 --> 00:16:47,080
I said it's just a scratch!

414
00:16:47,080 --> 00:16:49,940
That'll only get bacteria in it!

415
00:16:50,370 --> 00:16:52,290
This's a shortcut home!

416
00:16:52,290 --> 00:16:55,490
Yet another unproductive day...

417
00:16:56,290 --> 00:16:58,700
Day after day I play with kids,

418
00:16:58,700 --> 00:17:00,650
but don't get anything out of it.

419
00:17:00,650 --> 00:17:04,330
Is it really okay to just wait
for inspiration to strike?

420
00:17:05,050 --> 00:17:07,310
The deadline keeps drawing closer...

421
00:17:07,310 --> 00:17:08,170
Closer...

422
00:17:19,610 --> 00:17:20,380
There!

423
00:17:20,380 --> 00:17:21,370
That's it!

424
00:17:21,370 --> 00:17:22,970
The God of Calligraphy has descended!

425
00:17:23,630 --> 00:17:26,940
I never thought I'd find the
desire to write this easily!

426
00:17:27,530 --> 00:17:29,040
I have to rush home and write!

427
00:17:29,040 --> 00:17:30,520
Right now, I can do it!

428
00:17:34,870 --> 00:17:36,650
What's the matter, Naru?

429
00:17:36,650 --> 00:17:38,920
Sensei's not followin' us.

430
00:17:38,920 --> 00:17:41,280
He just went home a different
way without tellin' us.

431
00:17:41,480 --> 00:17:42,660
Ya may be right.

432
00:17:42,660 --> 00:17:43,710
I am right!

433
00:17:43,710 --> 00:17:45,470
Sensei's always like that.

434
00:17:45,470 --> 00:17:46,250
Yer right!

435
00:17:46,250 --> 00:17:47,220
Darn right!

436
00:17:51,470 --> 00:17:53,250
Sensei ain't home yet?!

437
00:17:53,470 --> 00:17:56,290
There wasn't anyone here when we came.

438
00:17:56,290 --> 00:17:58,230
On our way back from the mountain,

439
00:17:58,230 --> 00:17:59,720
Sensei just disappeared.

440
00:17:59,720 --> 00:18:01,640
Disappeared?

441
00:18:01,640 --> 00:18:03,390
I know what happened!

442
00:18:01,640 --> 00:18:04,270
I Want to
Be a Hermit

443
00:18:03,390 --> 00:18:07,460
A wild giant from the hills must've
trapped him and gobbled him up!

444
00:18:09,930 --> 00:18:14,010
Monster or not, it's still worrisome
that he hasn't returned yet.

445
00:18:14,010 --> 00:18:17,900
Even if he got lost in the hills,
the forest ain't that deep.

446
00:18:18,410 --> 00:18:19,190
There!

447
00:18:23,130 --> 00:18:23,950
Just a rabbit?

448
00:18:24,590 --> 00:18:26,160
That scared me!

449
00:18:28,110 --> 00:18:30,640
And I finally felt like I could
write good calligraphy...

450
00:18:31,480 --> 00:18:37,250
The time I just spent playing
with the kids feels far in the past.

451
00:18:39,320 --> 00:18:40,380
This is bad!

452
00:18:40,380 --> 00:18:44,080
I'm panicking so much that my brain's
started to fabricate memories!

453
00:18:44,400 --> 00:18:46,600
Keep calm, keep calm.

454
00:18:46,600 --> 00:18:48,800
A little further up, and I'll be back on the path.

455
00:18:50,800 --> 00:18:52,630
You can do it, Seishuu!

456
00:18:52,780 --> 00:18:54,880
You can do it, Seishuu!

457
00:18:55,240 --> 00:18:56,300
All right!

458
00:19:02,250 --> 00:19:02,950
Ow!

459
00:19:03,160 --> 00:19:04,410
This can't be happening...

460
00:19:05,990 --> 00:19:08,210
C'mon, cut it out already!

461
00:19:08,210 --> 00:19:09,470
Darn it!

462
00:19:09,330 --> 00:19:16,960
Pose to reduce surface area
in contact with ground

463
00:19:09,470 --> 00:19:11,400
Isn't it about time someone came to rescue me?!

464
00:19:11,400 --> 00:19:12,910
What are they doing?

465
00:19:12,910 --> 00:19:14,860
Getting lost in the wilderness

466
00:19:14,860 --> 00:19:16,960
is the height of isolation!

467
00:19:17,840 --> 00:19:18,710
I'm going to die.

468
00:19:19,200 --> 00:19:21,680
I'm going to end up dying alone, literally.

469
00:19:22,650 --> 00:19:24,330
Somebody save me!

470
00:19:24,330 --> 00:19:26,340
I don't care who!

471
00:19:28,540 --> 00:19:29,420
What's that?

472
00:19:32,760 --> 00:19:34,680
What, it's just a key?

473
00:19:39,520 --> 00:19:41,160
It's a key to my house!

474
00:19:42,120 --> 00:19:43,160
The duplicate key?

475
00:19:43,160 --> 00:19:44,250
I lost it.

476
00:19:44,250 --> 00:19:46,410
Maybe while playin' in the hills out back?

477
00:19:46,530 --> 00:19:47,790
That girl...

478
00:19:51,450 --> 00:19:53,050
This is ridiculous!

479
00:19:53,050 --> 00:19:55,730
What am I freaking out about?
I'm in the hills behind my house!

480
00:19:55,730 --> 00:19:58,710
Who the heck gets hopelessly
lost in his own backyard?

481
00:20:03,570 --> 00:20:04,600
What's this?

482
00:20:05,820 --> 00:20:07,430
Amazing...

483
00:20:07,430 --> 00:20:09,410
Is this outer space?

484
00:20:10,330 --> 00:20:11,290
A shooting star!

485
00:20:12,110 --> 00:20:13,850
Please fix my bath. Please fix my bath.

486
00:20:13,850 --> 00:20:15,360
Please fix my bath!

487
00:20:16,290 --> 00:20:18,020
No, that's not it.

488
00:20:18,410 --> 00:20:20,990
Please let me get home soon
and write calligraphy!

489
00:20:23,120 --> 00:20:25,750
See? I told ya he fell off the edge.

490
00:20:25,750 --> 00:20:28,320
No wonder he wasn't on the
usual paths when we looked.

491
00:20:28,320 --> 00:20:31,990
Sensei, I'm so glad yer safe!

492
00:20:32,710 --> 00:20:33,620
Sheesh!

493
00:20:33,900 --> 00:20:35,110
What took you so long?

494
00:20:35,490 --> 00:20:37,300
Is Sensei cryin'?

495
00:20:37,300 --> 00:20:38,550
Yes, he is...

496
00:20:46,580 --> 00:20:47,970
Yes! It's finally come!

497
00:20:47,970 --> 00:20:48,950
Sensei!

498
00:20:48,950 --> 00:20:50,310
I brought the first aid...

499
00:20:50,310 --> 00:20:51,980
Here! It's here!

500
00:20:51,980 --> 00:20:53,920
He's in the middle of work.

501
00:20:57,690 --> 00:20:59,440
Seishuu
Handa

502
00:20:59,440 --> 00:21:00,320
Seishuu
Handa

503
00:21:00,230 --> 00:21:02,070
STAR

504
00:21:02,590 --> 00:21:05,650
As I thought, inspiration really is important.

505
00:22:41,250 --> 00:22:42,060
Yeah.

506
00:22:42,710 --> 00:22:43,760
I see.

507
00:22:44,190 --> 00:22:45,800
Yeah, got it.

508
00:22:46,680 --> 00:22:47,920
I'll come home.
